# XRPL Wave Machine — Project Rules

## What this is
A gamified discovery & activation layer for the XRP Ledger, built for the
XRPL Commons "Make Waves on XRPL" buildathon (Jun 21 – Sep 21, 2026).
Users spin (Category → App → Mission), complete a real action in a live
XRPL app, and Wave Machine verifies it against public mainnet history.

## Non-negotiable invariants — never violate these
1. READ-ONLY & NON-CUSTODIAL. This app never holds keys, never signs,
   never constructs transactions for users. Verification reads public
   `account_tx` history only. Xaman sign-in is identity-only (SignIn
   pseudo-transaction via PKCE).
2. NOT A WAGERING SYSTEM. Spins are free and rate-limited. Never add
   any mechanic where users deposit value for a chance at more value.
   Rewards come from verified actions, never random outcomes.
3. ANTI-FARMING. Repeat completions of the same mission earn 0 XP.
   Leaderboards rank unique verified missions, never raw transaction
   volume. This directly satisfies the Commons Code of Conduct ban on
   metric manipulation / sybil / wash activity — treat it as load-bearing.
4. TRUST TRANSPARENCY. Every app shows verification status
   (Community Submitted / Developer Verified / Mainnet Activity Verified)
   and risk info BEFORE the user starts. Sponsored placement must always
   be disclosed; never present paid placement as organic.
5. MAINNET. The competition requires live mainnet products. Do not add
   testnet-only paths as the primary flow.

## Architecture
- src/App.jsx        — all views (Discover/Mission/Passport/Leaderboard/Apps/Devs)
- src/data/ecosystem.js — CATEGORIES, APPS (+missions), BADGE_DEFS, mock leaders
- src/lib/xrpl.js    — read-only WebSocket helpers (account_info, account_tx matcher)
- src/hooks/useXaman.js — QR sign-in (PKCE); degrades to manual r-address entry

Verification model: missions verify by TRANSACTION TYPE in the user's own
history (Payment, TrustSet, OfferCreate, AMMDeposit, NFTokenMint,
NFTokenAcceptOffer, AccountSet) after mission start time — no designated
destination addresses, nothing custodial to maintain.

## Stack & conventions
- Vite + React 18 + Tailwind (core utilities) + lucide-react icons.
- Aesthetic: mission-control / HUD. Deep space navy (#060614 bg, #0b0b22
  panels), neon cyan (#22d3ee) / purple (#a855f7) / fuchsia accents,
  font-mono uppercase tracking-widest for HUD labels.
  NOT: RPG skins, skill trees, fake game mechanics, visual clutter.
- State is currently in-memory (useState). Next milestone: Supabase
  persistence for users/apps/missions/completions/spins (schema in README).
- Secrets discipline: VITE_XAMAN_API_KEY is public-safe; the Xaman API
  SECRET and any Anthropic keys live only in Vercel server env vars.

## When asked to add features
- Server-side verification (Vercel API routes) should mirror src/lib/xrpl.js
  and add per-IP + per-wallet rate limiting (same pattern as the
  XRPL Control Room api/ai.ts proxy).
- Keep copy plain and safety-forward: estimated time, cost, risk, and
  "never asks for your keys" language stays on every mission screen.
